	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just a quick question for you all out there.&nbsp;&nbsp;Recently I have been soloing snow cougars in Iceclad and have noticed a strange thing and would like to hear some input on it.  Typically at the end of a fight, the cougar is dead and I've been whacked for about 2 bubbles of life. I've done this so many times that getting below two bubbles from max is extremely rare. This is with NO BUFFS.  I had a cleric friend of mine visit one day while soloing and he gave me the typical HP and AC buffs (he's in his low to mid 30s).  After that he logged.  My HPs were in the 1400 range and my AC was up a proportional amount.  I started soloing the cougars again thinking I'd be belting out several now that I had so many more HPs and a much higher AC, but <br>noticed after taking them on I was still getting hit for about 2 bubbles of life by the end of the fight. Now I started wondering what was going on?  My Hps were up about 300 or so from my normal amount (not to mention my AC) but yet I was still getting hit for two bubbles each fight.  How is this possible?  I was hitting them for my normal amount and the fights were taking the usual amount of time to complete. What up??<br>If anyone else has noticed this, I'd like to hear about it.  If anyone has any ideas why this happens, I'd also like to hear about it becuase I'm beginning to wonder what good buffs are if you get hit for the same number of bubbles per fight as you did prior to having the buff.<br><br>Be well and be safe!<br>Burgen Battleblood<br>Dwarven Paladin of the 39th Season<br>Hands of Norrath<br>Zebuxork Server<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Burgen Battleblood Paladin of the 52nd Season<br>Realm Powers<br>Zebuxoruk Server</td></tr>
