	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Burgen,<br><br>I believe you have raised an interesting point and something that I have wondered about for some time. I would like to think that your AC and HP buffs weren't of sufficient strength to truly show much of a difference.&nbsp;&nbsp;But, I have noticed throughout my 1000's of fights to date, many with the same opponent over and over and over again, that regardless of how well I hit, the battle always ends up about the same. <br><br>I have often wondered if there was some SET Ratio that compares your level/abilities/etc. to the mobs level/abilities/etc. and comes up with some foregone conclusion or predetermined outcome of how the battle was going to turn out. <br><br>For example: If you are really hammering the mob, the mob will suddenly start hitting you for more points...and you will start missing more often to bring the &quot;Ratio&quot; back into some pre-set balance.  Likewise, if the mob is pounding you, suddenly he starts missing more and you start missing less.  I have no information to support this one way or the other, but I have definitely noticed it with mobs that I fight repeatedly...as you did with the Snow Cougars.<br><br>I have found that Haste definitely seems to change the outcome of battles, as well as significant Damage Shields.  But just straight hit pts and armor class, I have been hard pressed to see much of a difference. Even with big hit pt buffs like Talisman of Kragg and Riotous Health.  I can enhance my hit pts by hundreds, yet the outcome when I solo a blue wyvern in Cobalt Scar is about the same.<br><br>You are not alone in this event you have preceived, but unfortunately, I have no information to dispell or confirm what you suspect.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Cavalier<br><br>&quot;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&quot;<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
