	   <tr><td colspan=2>At higher levels a paladin can taunt a mob off of your chanter or wizard that overburns better than a warrior.&nbsp;&nbsp;I use a combination of chain stunning (level 30 &amp; 49 spells), root, taunt and flash of light. Every time I get the agro before the warrior.  The problem is that sometimes this will build up so much agro that it's hard to get the mob back on the main tank.<br><br>At low levels you are limited to taunt and flash of light but here is a trick to get in an extra taunt.  Set up a macro on a hot key to do the following 3 steps:  attack off, beg, attack on.  Begging acts as a taunt that you can use while waiting for your taunt key to refresh.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
