<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100707334872788></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100707334872788><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100707334872788>art of pulling???</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100707334872788#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61865><span id= >Sir Lumlaien</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>27 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Nov 29th 5:35 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here is a few tips for fellow pullers...lol<br><br>The art of pulling...<br><br>The art of pulling is not by any means easy or the same for any areas of even the same dungeon.&nbsp;&nbsp;The need for research outside of the game cannot be impressed enuff on everyone in the eq game...you need to know what to expect...where to zone...what it's like pulling...problems you may encounter...what loot is on what mobs...nothing worse than not doing the legwork on research and underestimate a mob and it's loot potential.  Is it a common/rare/very rare drop on a common/rare/very rare/triggered mob...etc etc etc  Other things to always be aware of is as follows:<br><br>1)  Pathing:  Meaning if you pull a mob, will it run straight to you or will it aggro more by running some insane pathing area you are not aware of and training more than your single pull?<br>Are you new to zone or a veteran puller in this area with these mobs?  How far is zone, in case you need too.  If you pull to many and know death is INC if you try to take them to party...do you train to zone, die and get a CR/rez, or KILL YOUR WHOLE GROUP?  Last option is least liked btw...LOL<br><br>2)  Aggro Radius:  If a mob is KOS to you...will it attack or only when you sit down?  Will others aggro from rooms or areas nearby that you are unaware of?<br><br>3)  Train handling capacity:  What can your group feasibly handle as a group before a casualty is caused and you are now on CR duty for a fellow party member?  If you do not have a healer in any sized group...then trains equal death...sooner or later.<br><br>4)  Group Mana Status:  Do you know what, if any, mana your group's casters are at?  Is healer at FM or OOM?  Is that wiz/mage/necro/chanter gonna have enuff mana to save your group from a bad pull or did you just sign everyone's CR ticket?<br>Do you know if the mobs you are pulling are too high for your casters to help you on, cuz if that's the case...you just turned a bunch of casters into Tanks and that's not a pretty sight by any means.<br><br>5)  AFK status:  Is your group all there?  Is the chanter getting a soda?  The cleric in the bathroom?  Or the other tanks afk?  Just because you are in a group and wanting xps is no excuse to be caught with your pants down for not asking the group?  IS EVERYONE RDY FOR A PULL?  IS EVERYONE BACK OR WE WAITING?  Pulling 3 mobs to an AFK group is the surest way to anger your party, kill yourself since no is around to help get the mobs that are beating you to death like a rag doll, and begin your way to a long and lengthy CR.<br><br>6)  Bind status:  Is your entire group binded in the closest zone or did they forget?  I was once in a group where no one but me bothered to bind in a nearby zone.  "Why bother we have a cleric with rez?"  Well...the cleric was the first to die and then everyone else but me.  I was smart and moved the cleric to zone area.  Everyone else kept pulling away and died.<br>I didn't stay with that group for too long after that.   Btw...cleric's bind pt was in FV...LOL<br><br>7)  Rdy status:  Is your group rdy for you to pull?  How many mobs can you pull?  Killing one mob fast or 8 mobs slowly is a choice best decided beforehand.  No chanter to mez?  Then 1-3 mobs at most.  Chanter with FM...whose Mez's stick...pull 1-5 mobs if you can handle it.  DON'T HAVE A CLUE ON HOW MANY TO PULL?  simple pull one single and work up from there.<br>Nothing is worse than the entire group looking around for you as your health bar looks like this one min ========== and then goes to this == with them saying, "WTF...ARE YOU PULLING?"  No one can save you, cuz no one has a clue where you are, what you pulled, or how many you pulled.<br><br>  Designated puller:  This should either be the highest lvl tank...highest ac/hp tank...this consideration should be based on NO buffs whatsoever?  Why?  Cuz sooner or later those buffs will vanish and usually do at the most inconvenient time also I might add.  Let me add this one final word of caution:  NO ONE & I MEAN NO ONE SHOULD PULL EXCEPT THE DESIGNATED PULLER.  Roamers and adds from aggro are one thing that are considered a way of life.  Surest way to step out of line in a group is to not be the designated puller and pull something.  I have seen it happen...it is not a nice feeling to see someone give you an add with an INC pull on the way.  E.g., I was in DL...A rogue was running around picking pockets like crazy in our group and trying the proc on his new dagger.  I was designated puller.  I pull single spider, get add giant...add spider...not bad i'm thinking...i got a chanter and full group with 2 healers.  When lo and behold as i run back and see this on chat channel... "WTF...who trained us?  OMG...why do we have 3 spiders nuking us?"  Needless to say... I had to kite my mobs around for a bit until it was safe to run my pull back to group.  SoW drops...oh oh ...hit jboots ...wait...can't...WTF!!!  I'm ROOTED   ARGH.... Loading Please Wait..."    Needless to say..the group disbanded regrouped and rogue was no longer with us.  End of story.  <br><br>While this is not a definitive guide to pulling in the least, I am only mentioning some of the most important aspects that one should be aware of.  HOTKEYS and their use for rdy for pull, mana status, INC %T should be in every pullers social keys. <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
