	   <tr><td colspan=2>In my humble opinion Paladins are neither weak, nor boring, nor are they useless to a group. Paladins are warriors that can actually take care of themselves. <br><br>For example:<br>Clerics (should) just sit back and heal and run when things get bad. Boring.<br><br>Warriors click autoattack and then occasionaly click kick/bash/whatever and run when things get bad. Boring.<br><br>Casters just sit back and, well, cast (ohhh look at the pretty colors) and die when things get bad. Weak and boring.<br><br>Rangers..ok they look like they would be pretty cool to play.<br><br>Druids again sit back and cast/heal and run REALY fast when things get bad. weak and weedy.<br><br>Paladins click autoattack, click bash (if your are 1h), cast spells to hurt/piss off monsters, and when things get bad? We got LoH! A real good thing when everyone else has runs (yup even that silly warrior who probably pulled to many creatures in the first place) because, and I know this is hard for some non paladins to believe why we would do it: you decided to stand firm that extra few seconds to let the rest of the group get away before you yourself run. Of course I like to test faith and try to finish the mob off if I can. Good bragging rights and all. And when its all said and done? Your the one standing gaurd over the group while the casters and healers mezz, and the warriors resting ( or has gotten bored and run off to pull something before everyones ready). So please don't tell me the Paladins are weak, boring, or useless to a group! <br><br>By the way I also Solo a lot Paladins are great at that to!<br><br>This has been my 2cp.<br><br>Torec<br>Paladin of Tunare<br>Luclin<br>"For the Glory of Tunare!"<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
