	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 28th 12:16 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.95]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Jcasetnl,<br><br>As a player who undertook the Armor of Ro Quests before Ry'gorr was invented, my advice is, persue the quests if you want to enjoy the adventure and complexities involved in the quest...with the nice armor being secondary.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Armor of Ro quests are a pain in the keester, no doubt about it, and if you look strictly at the armor itself, then it's probably not worth it. As you mentioned, Ry'Gorr is just about as good. However, if you look at the overall experience of the quests, it very well may be worth it depending on your playing objectives.<br><br>Personally, I enjoyed them. While doing the Armor of Ro quests I realized that I really LIKED doing quests and have embarked on many others since then because I enjoy doing them...not so much because of the end-item reward.<br><br>At level 30, you will find the quests very tough to do solo if not impossible. Obtaining the No-Drop Mistmoore Granite will be impossible solo at level 30.  To get the granite you have to actually go INSIDE the castle and Castle Mistmoore is a very daunting place.  This will take a good group of 30-ish players.  Having said that, MM became and still is one of my all-time favorite zones in the game.  I love the look and feel of the place. So persuing my Mistmoore Granite as part of the Ro quest also introduced me to a wonderful zone where I spent lots of time in my younger days. It's a tough zone. Many people hate it. But I found it quite a challenge and fun.<br><br>The Melatite will also prove to be a challenge. I spent lots of time in Sol A auctioning to buy drops of melatite. I didn't want to ruin my faction with the gnomes so I bought all of mine. While I loved Mistmoore I hated Sol A as a zone (just personal preference...I'm sure it is a fine zone for many) so I didn't like spending much time there.<br><br>Some of the Ro Pieces are better than others.  You may just want to do some of them, instead of all of them.  My personal favorites were:<br><br>Vambraces of Ro (No way you can handle the Plague Shark solo at level 30)<br>Boots of Ro<br>Helm of Ro<br>Greaves of Ro<br><br>You can easily skip the bracers, gauntlets and breastplate.<br><br>Just something to consider. Do them for the quest...not for the armor.<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Cavalier<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
