	   <tr><td colspan=2>Doh!&nbsp;&nbsp;Well, the last time I used AOL was about six months ago.  I know the horror stories you mention because I'm a techie and dealt with many an AOL problem.  For me I didn't have so many problems but often times I breeze through things that can be daunting to others and may not have considered them.  But FWIW, I must say that I was genuinely surprised at the quality of service from AOL the last time I used it.  In years past AOL meant surfing at a snale's pace but my last experience was very acceptable.  When I cancelled the service I was on hold for about twenty minutes but when it was done it was history and I didn't have a problem.  On the telemarketing thing, yeah, I guess that could be a problem I also didn't consider.  But again, being a techie I get those by default.  <br><br>So given that, don't use aol if you don't want to but if you do know of an ISP that offers a free trial period, even if only a week, go with that as opposed to paying for, at a minimum, a full month of service just to try the 'experiment' I mentioned above.  <br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
