	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.41]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well I just got lvl 30 and decided to pay Driana Prox in the freeport tunnels a visit.&nbsp;&nbsp;I figured with stun she would be cake now.  But with no practice with it she sent me running to EC like a little girl.  <br><br>Also, her pet was a real pain.  In the past I've heard you root the pet and go to town on the caster.  Interupt casting, etc.  But in practice I found that unless I ran *far* away, she would stay by the pets side.  And while I was running I was getting her DDs like crazy or she'd get a fear off.  <br><br>On the third attempt I went with spook the dead.  Casts a little faster and the pet immediately stops attacking, as opposed to me having to get out of range.  That worked like a champ and I then started to pour the stuns on like a cheap perfume and used bash during the recast pause.  She then resorted to punching me with her pretty little fists before crumpling in a heap at my feat.  <br><br>So am I missing something with the root method?  It would seem that any smart caster, especially in PvP, would just hang out by the pet when rooted and cast away.  Sure you can FoL the caster but if he's hotkeyed that won't make a difference.  Plus, assuming it's a necro, even if you fear and then root to get the pet away, the necro has a good five to six seconds to cast for free, can rejoin the pet, etc.  What do you guys do?<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
