	   <tr><td colspan=2>Whenever i am fighting undead outdoors or am dueling necros, i use spook because its just faster, less mana, and easier. Take "fear kiting" spectres in oasis for example. I would usually pull 2, spook one and root him, then fear/beat the crap out of the other one, and keep the one that is not hurt rooted. Then after the first one would die i would heal and then jump back in with fear. Fear is generally better when fighting undead cuz thats all we can fear = ).<br><br>I use root for normal MoBs when i need to back off for a heal or stop a vital runner. For Driana, i would start off with a fear on her pet if you feel its needed, then root driana and pound her. Then the pet will be a piece of cake. That is what i do for dueling necros.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
